The paper deals with the development of algorithms for detecting turbo-coded offset QPSK signals in the presence of frequency and clock offsets and AWGN. This involves techniques for synchronization, detection, and estimation, which are all related to information theory and communication systems (cs.IT, cs.COMM). The use of up-sampling, matched filtering, and differential correlation approach at the receiver also suggests a focus on digital signal processing and data structures (cs.DS). The proposed techniques are also well-suited for software implementation, indicating a potential interest in networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with the performance analysis of the proposed techniques, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
